UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 AN ACT relating to programs administered by the Department of Agriculture.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 247.234 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Every owner of an amusement ride or attraction business shall register the business
5 with the department annually.
6 (2) The business registration required by subsection (1) of this section shall be valid
7 until December 31 of the calendar year in which the registration is filed and shall be
8 issued upon payment of a registration fee, in accordance with administrative
9 regulations promulgated by the department.
10 (3) (a) No amusement ride or attraction shall be operated in this state without a
11 permit issued by the department to the owner of the amusement ride or
12 attraction. The permit shall be kept on site during the operation of the
13 amusement ride or attraction and viewable upon request.
14 (b) A permit shall be issued to each owner to operate the permitted amusement
15 ride or attraction in this state. A permit fee, which shall be determined by
16 administrative regulations promulgated by the department, shall be levied for
17 each amusement ride or attraction permit issued.
18 (c) The registrant shall furnish proof of liability insurance in effect on the
19 operation of each amusement ride or attraction providing coverage, with an
20 insurer authorized to issue a policy in this state, in the amount of not less than
21 one million dollars ($1,000,000) due to all bodily injuries or deaths per
22 occurrence, or in lieu thereof, if the applicant's amusement ride or amusement
23 attraction is one that is permanently located or erected on a site in this state,
24 the applicant shall be required only to provide proof of financial responsibility
25 in the sum of one million dollars ($1,000,000). Every registrant and
26 insurance carrier of these policies shall notify the department at least thirty
27 (30) days prior to cancellation of a policy for mobile amusement rides or
Page 1 of 13
HB005610.100 - 1210 - XXXX 1/28/2026 2:40 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 attractions and at least ten (10) days prior to cancellation of a policy for
2 permanent amusement rides or attractions.
3 (d) In addition to proof of adequate insurance coverage, the applicant shall
4 furnish any other information the department may require, including but not
5 limited to written notice of each intended operating site that will be open to
6 the general public to be received by the department at least fourteen (14) days
7 prior to operation at that site. In cases of emergency, notice of a change in
8 future plans may be given to the department by telephone.
9 (e) The department shall require an annual inspection of each amusement ride or
10 attraction before it may be operated in this state. Inspections performed by
11 department employees shall be subject to a fee based on the complexity of the
12 amusement ride or attraction and shall not be less than ten dollars ($10) or
13 more than five hundred dollars ($500). The cost of all inspections performed
14 by department employees shall be paid by the owner of the amusement ride or
15 attraction and shall[may] be prepaid[, but shall be paid no later than the day
16 of the inspection]. The department shall designate persons qualified by
17 education or experience, who are capable of determining amusement safety in
18 accordance with administrative regulations promulgated under KRS 247.232
19 to 247.236, as amusement safety inspectors. Any person who is not an
20 employee of the department and who is designated as an amusement safety
21 inspector shall register with the department and pay an annual registration fee,
22 which shall be determined by administrative regulations promulgated by the
23 department.
24 (f) A Kentucky inspection tag[permit seal] shall be affixed to every individual
25 amusement ride or attraction, or other location as determined by the
26 department, before it may be operated in this state. A Kentucky inspection tag
27 shall be valid for one (1) year from the date it was issued.
Page 2 of 13
HB005610.100 - 1210 - XXXX 1/28/2026 2:40 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 (4) (a) In addition to the inspection required in subsection (3)(e) of this section, the
2 department may inspect amusement rides and attractions without notice at any
3 time while operating in this state. There shall not be any charge for additional
4 inspections in which safety violations are not found. In regard to situations in
5 which safety violations are found, the department may charge an inspection
6 fee not to exceed five hundred dollars ($500) for any future inspection
7 necessary. The corrections of these safety violations shall comply with
8 accepted standards of safety, and shall be accomplished prior to operating the
9 equipment in this state.
10 (b) In regard to situations in which safety violations are found that cannot be
11 corrected immediately, the amusement ride or attraction shall cease to operate
12 in this state by order of the amusement safety inspector.[ In addition, the
13 amusement safety inspector shall conspicuously post a public notice on or
14 near the amusement ride or attraction. The notice shall adequately inform the
15 public of the safety violation present.]
16 (c) Any owner who continues to operate an amusement ride or attraction after an
17 order to cease operation has been issued shall have his or her business
18 registration suspended and the amusement ride or attraction permit revoked,
19 and may be subject to further penalties provided in KRS 247.233. In addition,
20 the county attorney of each county and the department are hereby authorized
21 to seek an injunction against the owner or operator of any amusement ride or
22 attraction being operated in violation of KRS 247.232 to 247.236.
23 (d) Revenue generated by this section and KRS 247.233 shall be used for the
24 implementation and administration of KRS 247.232 to 247.236; the balance,
25 if any, shall not lapse but shall be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
26 (5) (a) An owner of an amusement ride or attraction shall:
27 1. Conduct a pre-opening inspection and test of the ride or attraction prior
Page 3 of 13
HB005610.100 - 1210 - XXXX 1/28/2026 2:40 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 to admitting the public each day the ride or attraction is intended to be
2 used; and
3 2. Maintain for at least the previous twelve (12) months a signed record of
4 the required pre-opening inspections and tests and any other pertinent
5 information as required by the department.
6 (b) The department may revoke the registration of any owner who fails to conduct
7 the required pre-opening inspections and tests or to maintain the required
8 reports.
9 (6) All unpaid civil penalties assessed upon a person for violations of KRS 247.232 to
10 247.236 shall remain in effect and shall permanently remain on record with the
11 department regardless of whether the person:
12 (a) Operates amusement rides or attractions under his or her name, another name,
13 an assumed name, or as a sole proprietorship;
14 (b) Is employed by another person operating amusement rides individually, as a
15 sole proprietorship, or as part of a partnership or corporation; or
16 (c) Operates amusement rides or attractions as a member of a partnership or
17 corporation.
18 Section 2. KRS 251.355 is amended to read as follows:
19 (1) No person shall be or act as a grain dealer in the Commonwealth without holding a
20 valid grain dealer license issued by the department.
21 (2) No person shall engage in the business of buying grain from producers for resale,
22 milling, or processing in the Commonwealth without holding a valid grain dealer
23 license issued by the department; provided, however, that no license shall be
24 required in order to buy grain from sellers who are not producers of grain.
25 (3) No person shall be or act as a grain warehouse operator in the Commonwealth
26 without holding a valid grain warehouse operator license issued by the department.
27 (4) No person shall own, control, operate, or manage any public warehouse in which
Page 4 of 13
HB005610.100 - 1210 - XXXX 1/28/2026 2:40 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 grain is stored for compensation in the Commonwealth without holding a valid
2 grain warehouse operator license issued by the department.
3 (5) Any person who possesses unpaid-grain for more than thirty (30) days shall be
4 deemed to be acting as a grain warehouse operator and shall be subject to the
5 licensing and financial requirements for grain warehouse operators under the
6 provisions of this chapter.
7 (6) Licenses issued by the department shall be valid for a period of time not to exceed
8 one (1) year and shall expire on June 30 each year.
9 (7) A separate license shall be required for each facility in the Commonwealth.
10 (8) The board, in conjunction with the department, shall promulgate administrative
11 regulations setting forth a schedule of fees for licensed grain warehouse operators.
12 Any changes to the schedule of fees shall be approved by a majority vote of the
13 board. The schedule of fees shall be reviewed by the board at least one (1) time
14 every four (4) years. The annual increase in board-approved license fees shall be
15 limited to five percent (5%) and shall not exceed twenty percent (20%) over any
16 four (4) year period.
17 (9) The board, in conjunction with the department, shall promulgate administrative
18 regulations setting forth a schedule of fees for licensed grain dealers. Any changes
19 to the schedule of fees shall be approved by a majority vote of the board. The
20 schedule of fees shall be reviewed by the board at least one (1) time every four (4)
21 years. The annual increase in board-approved license fees shall be limited to five
22 percent (5%) and shall not exceed twenty percent (20%) over any four (4) year
23 period.
24 (10) The department shall have the authority to issue a notice of violation and assess a
25 civil fine pursuant to KRS 251.990, or suspend or revoke a license if the board or
26 department determines any person[the licensee] has violated a provision of this
27 chapter or any administrative regulation promulgated under this chapter.
