1 (11) Any person receiving a notice of violation may contest the notice by submitting to
2 the department a written request for a hearing in accordance with KRS Chapter
3 13B within thirty (30) days of receipt. Failure to request a hearing shall result in
4 the recipient's failure to exhaust administrative remedies and render the notice
5 final.
6 (12) Any person aggrieved by any final order of the department may appeal to the
7 Franklin Circuit Court or the Circuit Court of the county in which the
8 respondent is located, in accordance with KRS 13B.140.
9 (13) The department may enforce any final order by petitioning the Franklin Circuit
10 Court or the Circuit Court of the county in which the respondent is located.
11 Section 3. KRS 260.600 is amended to read as follows:
12 (1) Any person requiring a license may obtain an application by calling the Kentucky
13 Department of Agriculture, Division of Regulation and Inspection. A license may
14 be renewed when accompanied by a renewal application and the required fees. A
15 license for the current year shall not be issued if there are past due license fees and
16 penalties pending for previous years. With regard to shell egg dealers, wholesalers,
17 and packers, and specialty egg processors, dealers, and wholesalers, all of the
18 previous year's assessment fees shall be current before licenses shall be renewed.
19 Any person selling eggs without the required license will be subject to having the
20 eggs removed from sale until a license has been acquired.
21 (2) A license is required of each handler of eggs selling in the Commonwealth subject
22 to the exceptions specified in KRS 260.550. The annual license fees are as follows,
23 varying for dealers, distributors, wholesalers, producers, and packers, according to
24 the average weekly volume of the month in which the licensee handled the most
25 eggs during the preceding year:
26 (a) Retailers ................................................................................................$20.00
27 (b) Shell egg dealers, distributors, wholesalers, producers, and packers within
Page 6 of 13
HB005610.100 - 1210 - XXXX 1/28/2026 2:40 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 56/GA
1 Kentucky or out-of-state:
2 1-25 cases or 1-750 dozen ..............................................................$20.00
3 26-50 cases or 751-1500 dozen ......................................................$30.00
4 Over 50 cases or over 1500 dozen ..................................................$50.00
5 (c) Specialty egg processors, dealers, and wholesalers within
6 Kentucky or out-of-state .........................................................................$50.00.
7 (3) Any egg handler engaged in more than one (1) type of activity for which a license is
8 provided shall pay that license fee which is the highest of the licenses prescribed for
9 each type of activity in which he or she is engaged.
10 (4) All eggs bought or sold within the Commonwealth of Kentucky shall bear a two
11 cent ($0.02) assessment fee for each fifteen (15) dozen shell egg lot or portion
12 thereof. Pasteurized liquid and pasteurized frozen egg products shall be assessed a
13 fee of one-half (1/2) cent ($0.005) per ten (10) pound lot. Dried, dehydrated, hard-
14 cooked, or specialty egg products shall be assessed a fee of one cent ($0.01) per ten
15 (10) pound lot. These assessment fees shall be assessed and paid one (1) time as
16 agreed between responsible parties as the product moves through the distribution
17 network. All reports and fees are due monthly and shall be received by the
18 department prior to the fifteenth of the month following the month of activity,
19 unless there is an agreement with the department to report and pay these fees on a
20 quarterly, semi-annual, or annual basis. In this event, the reports and fees shall be
21 received prior to the fifteenth of the month following the period of activity.
22 (5) All licenses shall expire on January 31[April 1] of each year. Handlers having
23 more than one (1) place of business shall hold a license for each location. Licenses
24 shall not be transferred.
25 (6) Those that are exempt from licensing under KRS 260.550 are not exempt from
26 inspection, with the exception of consumers.[ The shell eggs or egg products used
27 by these persons are not exempt from the required assessment fee.]
