1 Section 4. KRS 246.220 is amended to read as follows:
2 (1) No person shall in any way hinder, refuse, or defeat entrance or inspection by an
3 agent or employee of the department who is performing the duties of his or her
4 office for the purpose of combating the European corn borer under subsection (1) of
5 KRS 246.210.
6 (2) No person shall interfere in any way with the department or any of its agents or
7 employees in the inspection of premises and livestock, or in the testing of livestock
8 on any premises when the object of the inspection or testing is to determine the
9 existence of, or to combat in any way, communicable disease in livestock. No
10 person shall interfere in any way with the department or any of its agents or
11 employees in the removal from any premises of livestock found to be infected with
12 a communicable disease.
13 (3) No person shall hinder the efforts of the state entomologist or his or her agents in
14 combating Japanese beetles under KRS 246.210.
15 (4) No person shall hinder the entomologist in the performance of any of his or her
16 duties.
17 (5) No person shall interfere in any way with inspectors or assistants while they are
18 discharging their duties under KRS 250.021 to 250.111.
19 (6) No person shall hinder, prevent, or attempt to prevent any person from discharging
20 his or her duties under KRS 250.491 to 250.631.
21 (7) No person shall in any way impersonate, hinder, or obstruct the department or its
22 inspectors in the performance of their official duties under KRS [248.280 to
23 248.440 or ]261.220.
24 Section 5. KRS 260.540 is amended to read as follows:
25 As used in KRS 260.540 to 260.650, unless the context otherwise requires:
26 (1) "Ambient temperature" means the atmospheric temperature surrounding or
27 encircling shell eggs;
