1 (2)[ "Board" means the Egg Marketing Board;
2 (3)] "Candle" means to determine the interior quality of a shell egg based on the use of a
3 candling light as defined in the USDA Handbook 75(7 CFR Part 56);
4 (3)[(4)] "Candled and graded" means candled and graded under state and federal
5 standards and regulations;
6 (4)[(5)] "Case" means a container of thirty (30) dozen shell eggs as used in
7 commercial practice in the United States. The term "half-case" shall mean a
8 container of fifteen (15) dozen eggs. Case also means any other quantity packaging
9 which is considered a wholesale pack;
10 (5)[(6)] "Check" means an egg that has a broken shell or a crack in the shell, but
11 whose membranes are intact and whose contents are not leaking;
12 (6)[(7)] "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Agriculture;
13 (7)[(8)] "Consumer" means all persons purchasing eggs for consumption and not
14 resale;
15 (8)[(9)] "Department" means the Department of Agriculture;
16 (9)[(10)] "Dealer" means a person, organization, or cooperative engaged in the business
17 of buying eggs from producers or other persons, either on his or her own account or
18 as an agent, and selling or transferring eggs by the case or other quantity to a
19 wholesaler, processor, retailer, specialty egg processor, or other persons or
20 consumers;
21 (10)[(11)] "Dirty egg" means an egg that has a shell that is unbroken and has adhering
22 dirt or foreign material, or prominent stains covering more than one-fourth (1/4) of
23 the shell surface;
24 (11)[(12)] "Distributor" means any person who sells, offers, or otherwise exposes shell
25 eggs or egg products to a wholesaler, retailer, or food service facility. "Distributor"
26 also means any person or producer who distributes shell eggs or egg products to his
27 or her own retail outlet, store, or food service facility;
