1 (12)[(13)] "Egg product" means processed and convenience forms of eggs for home and
2 commercial use, including hard-cooked, or specialty egg products and pasteurized
3 liquid, pasteurized frozen, or pasteurized dried egg products;
4 (13)[(14)] "FDA" means the Federal Food and Drug Administration;
5 (14)[(15)] "Handler" means a dealer, packer, processor, wholesaler, distributor, or
6 retailer;
7 (15)[(16)] "Inedible" means an egg that is unfit for human food in whole or in part,
8 addled or moldy, containing black rot, white rot, blood ring, adherent yolks, or
9 bloody whites, incubated beyond the blood ring stage, or consisting to any extent of
10 filthy decomposed substance. This also includes any eggs unfit for human
11 consumption due to causes other than those listed in this subsection;
12 (16)[(17)] "Leaker" means an egg that has a crack or break in the shell and shell
13 membranes to the extent that the egg contents are exposed or are exuding or free to
14 exude through the shell;
15 (17)[(18)] "Loss" means an egg that is unfit for human food because it is smashed or
16 broken so that its contents are leaking; or overheated, frozen, or contaminated; or an
17 incubator reject; or contains a bloody white, large meat spots, a large quantity of
18 blood, or other foreign material;
19 (18)[(19)] "Lot" means any given quantity of two (2) or more eggs of a named grade,
20 billed on an invoice or inspected by the department;
21 (19)[(20)] "Lot consolidation" means the removal of damaged eggs from consumer
22 labeled cartons and replacement of the damaged eggs with eggs of the same grade,
23 size, sell-by date, brand, lot, and source;
24 (20)[(21)] "Packer" means any person who grades, sizes, candles, and packs eggs for
25 purposes of sale;
26 (21)[(22)] "Person" means any individual, firm, partnership, corporation, company,
27 association, or any other type of business entity that traffics in, handles, or sells
